{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5120d63b-c38d-4684-9c9b-690369c52eb4","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll give you guidance based on the skill-validator framework referenced in this repo.\n\n## Evaluation File Format\n\nCreate an `evaluation.yml` at your plugin root. Each entry is a scenario with a user prompt and expected outcomes:\n\n```yaml\n- description: \"Search by category\"\n  prompt: \"Find all electronics under $50\"\n  expectedToolCalls:\n    - toolName: searchProducts\n      parameters:\n        category: \"electronics\"\n        maxPrice: 50\n  expectedResponseContains:\n    - \"electronics\"\n\n- description: \"Product detail lookup\"\n  prompt: \"Show me the details for product ID 12345\"\n  expectedToolCalls:\n    - toolName: getProductDetails\n      parameters:\n        productId: \"12345\"\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n**Cover these categories:**\n\n1. **Direct lookups** — \"Get details for product X\" (tests basic tool invocation)\n2. **Filtered searches** — \"Find red shoes under $30\" (tests multiple parameter binding)\n3. **Multi-step reasoning** — \"Compare the cheapest laptop to the most expensive one\" (tests chaining tool calls)\n4. **Ambiguity handling** — \"Find something good for a birthday gift\" (tests graceful behavior with vague input)\n5. **Edge cases** — \"Search for a product that doesn't exist\" (tests error handling)\n\n**Tips:**\n- Each scenario should test **one capability** clearly\n- Include both **happy path** and **failure** cases\n- Vary parameter combinations to cover your tool's full surface area\n- Add scenarios where the LLM should choose the **right tool** among several\n- Keep prompts realistic — phrase them how a real user would\n\nSee `eng/skill-validator/src/docs/InvestigatingResults.md` (when present) for details on interpreting results and the results JSON schema.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a84211e6-7c8d-48d3-a3c9-e303581a454c","reasoningOpaque":"",